---
/**
 * ai-infrastructure/0001 · Figure 3 — Module 2, the bi-encoder /
 * "Meaning becomes position; closeness becomes distance".
 * Verbatim from the source HTML. Uses marker-end="url(#arw)" (def from Fig1).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A bi-encoder embeds documents at ingest and the query at search time, then compares vectors by distance; meaning maps to position in vector space."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Meaning becomes position; closeness becomes distance</text
        >

        <!-- ingest path -->
        <text x="40" y="46" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#6b675f">At ingest (once)</text>
        <rect x="40" y="54" width="120" height="28" rx="5" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">documents</text>
        <line x1="160" y1="68" x2="196" y2="68" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="198" y="54" width="120" height="28" rx="5" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="258" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >embedding model</text
        >
        <line x1="318" y1="68" x2="354" y2="68" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="356" y="54" width="140" height="28" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="426" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >vectors &rarr; indexed</text
        >

        <!-- query path -->
        <text x="40" y="106" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#6b675f"
            >At query (per request)</text
        >
        <rect x="40" y="114" width="120" height="28" rx="5" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">the query</text>
        <line x1="160" y1="128" x2="196" y2="128" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="198" y="114" width="120" height="28" rx="5" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="258" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >same model</text
        >
        <line x1="318" y1="128" x2="354" y2="128" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="356" y="114" width="140" height="28" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="426" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >one query vector</text
        >

        <!-- vector space -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="160"
            width="560"
            height="72"
            rx="8"
            fill="color-mix(in srgb,#b5179e 5%,transparent)"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
        <text x="55" y="178" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e">vector space</text>
        <circle cx="160" cy="205" r="5" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="160"
            y="224"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            fill="#6b675f">"refund"</text
        >
        <circle cx="180" cy="198" r="5" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="200"
            y="194"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            fill="#6b675f">"money back"</text
        >
        <circle cx="172" cy="210" r="6" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="172"
            y="194"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">query</text
        >
        <circle cx="470" cy="200" r="5" fill="#9a2417"></circle><text
            x="470"
            y="219"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            fill="#6b675f">"GPU spec"</text
        >
        <text x="360" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >near = similar meaning &middot; far = unrelated</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A <em>bi-encoder</em> embeds each document independently, so the corpus is pre-computed and indexed
        offline. At query time you embed only the query and compare — that asymmetry is what makes vector
        search feasible at scale.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2b">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
